From Eric Dujardin Subject Re Accented How I've been able to configure xterm so that I can type in accented I'm using with fonts my shell is tcsh with the following definitions setenv LC CTYPE iso stty Then I add the following in my file XTerm eightBitInput True XTerm eightBitOutput True XTerm override Meta Key ' keymap aigu n Meta Key keymap grave n Meta Key keymap circ n Meta Key keymap ced XTerm Shift Key e string keymap None n Key E string keymap None n Shift Key c string n Key C string XTerm Shift Key e string keymap None n Key E string keymap None n Shift Key u string keymap None n Key U string keymap None n Shift Key a string keymap None n Key A string keymap None XTerm Shift Key e string keymap None n Key E string keymap None n Shift Key u string keymap None n Key U string keymap None n Shift Key i string keymap None n Key I string keymap None n Shift Key o string keymap None n Key O string keymap None XTerm Shift Key c string keymap None n Key C string keymap None This makes the Meta ' keys behave as dead Of course this only works for For emacs my solution is to install the Lucid version of GnuEmacs and to load the x compose Hope this helps Eric Eric Dujardin INRIA Rocquencourt projet RODIN Les bons gongs font BP Le Chesnay Cedex les bonzes amis Tel Gotlib